# uztagger

https://pypi.org/project/uzmorph <br>
https://github.com/UlugbekSalaev/uzmorph

uzmorph is focused to make morphological analyzer of Uzbek word based on morphemes and limited number of lexicon. The tool includes list of POS tagset, tagging method. 
It is created as a python library and uploaded to [PyPI](https://pypi.org/). It is simply easy to use in your python project or other programming language projects via the API. 

## About project
The tool is focused to make morphological analyzer of Uzbek word based on morphemes.

## Quick links

- [Github](https://github.com/UlugbekSalaev/uzmorph)
- [PyPI](https://pypi.org/project/uzmorph/)
- [Web-UI](https://nlp.urdu.uz/?menu=uzmorph)

## Demo

You can use [web interface](http://nlp.urdu.uz/?menu=uzmorph).

## Features

- Morphological Analysing 
- POS tag list
- Help function

## Usage

Three options to run uzmorph:

- pip
- API 
- Web interface

### pip installation

To install uzmorph, simply run:

```code
pip install uzmorph
```

After installation, use in python like following:
```yml
# import the library
from uzmorph import Morph
# create an object 
tagger = Tagger()
# call tagging method
tagger.pos_tag('Bizlar bugun maktabga bormoqchimiz.')
# output
[('Bizlar','NOUN'),('bugun', 'NOUN'), ('maktabga', 'NOUN'), ('bormoqchimiz', 'VERB'), ('.', 'PUNC')]
```

### API
API configurations: 
 - Method: `GET`
 - Response type: `string`
 - URL: `https://nlp.urdu.uz:8080/uzmorph/pos_tag`
   - Parameters: `text:string`
 - Sample Request: `https://nlp.urdu.uz:8080/uzmorph/pos_tag?text=Ular%20maktabga%20borayaptilar.`
 - Sample output: `[("Ular","NOUN"),("maktabga",""),("borayaptilar",""),(".","PUNC")]`

### Web-UI

The web interface created to use easily the library:
You can use web interface [here](http://nlp.urdu.uz/?page=uzmorph).

![Demo image](src/uzmorph/web-interface-ui.png)

### POS tag list
Tagger using following options as POS tag:<br>
    `NOUN`  Noun {Ot}<br>
    `VERB`  Verb {Fe'l}<br>
    `ADJ `  Adjective {Sifat}<br>
    `NUM `  Numeric {Son}<br>
    `ADV `  Adverb {Ravish}<br>
    `PRN `  Pronoun {Olmosh}<br>
    `CNJ `  Conjunction {Bog'lovchi}<br>
    `ADP `  Adposition {Ko'makchi}<br>
    `PRT `  Particle {Yuklama}<br>
    `INTJ`  Interjection {Undov}<br>
    `MOD `  Modal {Modal}<br>
    `IMIT`  Imitation {Taqlid}<br>
    `AUX `  Auxiliary verb {Yordamchi fe'l}<br>
    `PPN `  Proper noun {Atoqli ot}<br>
    `PUNC`  Punctuation {Tinish belgi}<br>
    `SYM `  Symbol {Belgi}<br>

### Result Explaining

The method ```pos_tag``` returns list, that an item of the list contain tuples for each token of the text with following format: ```(token, pos)```, for POS tag list, see <i>POS Tag List</i> section on above.  
#### Result from `tagger` method
`[('Bizlar','NOUN'),('bugun', 'NOUN'), ('maktabga', 'NOUN'), ('bormoqchimiz', 'VERB'), ('.', 'PUNC')]`

